The core design is now visible: each queued/direct operation captures `{userId, farmId, local generation/token, serverEpoch}`, binds the captured identity and epoch into the eventual PostgREST/Storage request, and re-verifies after remote acceptance before changing memory, queue, receipt, or public success. I’m now checking each repository for any path that skips one of those stages and each SQL function for equivalent server-side enforcement.
