The queue/cache pass uncovered a second cross-account race: several read wrappers capture Farm A, then call a live repository that re-resolves the current session; after an A→B replacement they can return B’s rows to the old A operation and write them into A’s offline-cache key. The existing regressions fence writes and shell rendering, but I have not found a read/cache race proof yet; I’m validating the precise affected paths before assigning final severity.
